commentary: Kumar to Simmons, OUT horror shot from Simmons, he has combusted with an ugly-looking top-edge that's ended in mid-off's hands. He had decided early that he was advancing down the track, and Praveen had enough time to see him and drop it short. Simmons then threw his hands at an attempted pull, though he was in no position for it. It took the top-edge and looped into Harbhajan's hands.

commentary: Mishra to Edwards, 1 run poor effort from Harbhajan at midwicket. Edwards has no idea what Mishra is up to. This one was tossed well up in leg stump, and Edwards approaches it as if he is checking if there's a snake under a toppled basket. He plays an awry whip and the leading edge balloons up. Harbhajan runs back, but doesn't move fast enough and can't get his hands to it as it drops over his right shoulder.

Poor, poor shot.

commentary: Harbhajan Singh to Baugh, no run very full outside off, Baugh looks to drive away from the body, but doesn't get it away. Parthiv collects and appeals for a catch, Harbhajan joins in the appeal late. The umpire Peter Nero initially says not out, and then chooses to check with his colleague. And they finally decide to go to the third umpire. Well, well. The bat went close to the turf as Baugh swung. No real evidence that the bat hit the ball, or if it hit the pitch. No noise either, other than that of the ball pitching before he played the shot. Has to be not out. Well, they have spent a real long time checking on this. Has the third umpire nodded off? Green light comes on. Celebrations. Time hasn't stopped on us!

commentary: Kumar to Rampaul, FOUR runs Praveen finishes with a ball too slow even for slower balls.
